The Team Manager of Lobi Stars football club of Makurdi, Barnabas Imenger, is dead . The former Super Eagles player died after a protracted illness in Abuja. He played for former Hawks FC of Makurdi, which later became BBC FC , Lobi Bank FC and Lobi stars football club. THE NATION learnt his corpse was being conveyed from Abuja to Makurdi. A statement by management of Lobi stars football explained burial date will be announced after consultation with the family .